<p>does anyone know how can I create tabs <strong>dynamically</strong> based on what is selected from a Listbox?</p>  <p>This is what I have:</p>  <p><strong>ListBox:</strong></p>  <pre><code>    &lt;asp:ListBox ID="SelectionListBox" runat="server" AppendDataBoundItems="True" SelectionMode="Multiple" Height="130px" Width="350px"&gt;     &lt;asp:ListItem Text="Apple" Value ="1"  /&gt;     &lt;asp:ListItem Text="Watermelon" Value ="2"  /&gt;     &lt;asp:ListItem Text="Kiwi" Value ="3"  /&gt;     &lt;asp:ListItem Text="Plum" Value ="4"  /&gt;     &lt;asp:ListItem Text="Pineapple" Value ="5"  /&gt; &lt;/asp:ListBox&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>RetrieveButton:</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;asp:Button ID="RetrieveButton" runat="server" Text="Button" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Based on what the user has selected from the Listbox, when the user pressed on the Retrieve button, number of tabs will be created based on the number of values user has selected from Listbox. </p>  <p>For example:</p>  <p>Let's say user has selected <strong>3 items</strong> from the Listbox and click on the button, <strong>3 tabs</strong> should be created at the bottom of the page on the <strong>same</strong> page with the tab names as the listbox items texts.</p>  <p><strong>Output:</strong></p>  <p>+----------------------------------+</p>  <pre><code>          ListBox         RetrieveButton </code></pre>  <p>+----------------------------------+</p>  <pre><code>           Tabs:  Apple | Watermelon | Kiwi </code></pre>  <p>+----------------------------------+</p>  <p>Any help is greatly appreciated. Thanks!</p>